How To properly package a boot.img for CM10 on Epic 4G (SPH-D700).

For native epic 4g radio/modem:
1 - Make any desired changes to the initramfs files in initramfs_er.
2 - Run the create_boot.img.sh script with the "er" arg.
    "./create_boot.img.sh er"

For crespo/nexus s 4g radio/modem:
<Credit & Source>
https://github.com/bbelos/android_device_samsung_epicmtd/commits/crespo-modem
https://github.com/xboxfanj/android_kernel_samsung_victory/commit/7f00332811efeb39e98e17c02d1d67e278dddd01
1 - Make any desired changes to the initramfs files in initramfs_nr.
2 - Run the create_boot.img.sh script with the nr arg.
    "./create_boot.img.sh nr"

3 - Create a flashable zip to install the newly created boot.img.

TWRP Recovery for Epic 4G
